    <div class="card">
      <h3>Europe Travel Notes</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Best general season:</strong> Late April–June and September–October offer pleasant temperatures, longer daylight, and fewer crowds than peak July–August. Scandinavia and Russia are best May–September.</li>
        <li><strong>Museum pre-booking:</strong> Major museums (Hermitage, Uffizi, Acropolis) require advance reservations in peak season. Book at least 2–3 weeks ahead.</li>
        <li><strong>Dress for churches:</strong> Covered shoulders and knees are required at Orthodox churches (Greece, Russia) and most Catholic churches (Italy, Croatia). Carry a lightweight layer.</li>
        <li><strong>River cruising tip:</strong> European river cruises sell out 12–18 months in advance for popular seasons. Christmas market cruises (November–December) sell out particularly fast.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

